Ubuntu 2 - Suricata IDS and Splunk Universal Forwarder Setup
Step 1: Update Packages
sudo apt update
________________________________________
Step 2: Install Suricata IDS
sudo apt install suricata -y
Wait until the installation completes.
________________________________________
Step 3: Verify Installation
suricata --version
Expected Output:
Suricata version information
________________________________________
Step 4: Start Suricata
sudo systemctl start suricata
________________________________________
Step 5: Enable Auto Start
sudo systemctl enable suricata
________________________________________
Step 6: Verify Status
sudo systemctl status suricata
Expected Output:
active (running)
________________________________________
Step 7: Verify Suricata Logs
ls /var/log/suricata/
Expected Output:
eve.json
fast.log
suricata.log
________________________________________
Step 8: Download Splunk Universal Forwarder
wget -O splunkforwarder.deb "https://download.splunk.com/products/universalforwarder/releases/10.2.3/linux/splunkforwarder-10.2.3-4d61cf8a5c0c-linux-amd64.deb"
________________________________________
Step 9: Install Splunk Universal Forwarder
sudo dpkg -i splunkforwarder.deb
________________________________________
Step 10: Start Splunk Universal Forwarder
sudo /opt/splunkforwarder/bin/splunk start --accept-license
Create credentials:
Username: ********
Password: ********
________________________________________
Step 11: Connect Forwarder to Splunk Server
sudo /opt/splunkforwarder/bin/splunk add forward-server 192.168.81.1:9997
Replace the IP address with your Splunk Server IP if different.
________________________________________
Step 12: Enable Boot Start
sudo /opt/splunkforwarder/bin/splunk enable boot-start
________________________________________
Step 13: Add Suricata Log Monitoring
sudo /opt/splunkforwarder/bin/splunk add monitor /var/log/suricata/eve.json
sudo /opt/splunkforwarder/bin/splunk add monitor /var/log/suricata/fast.log
________________________________________
Step 14: Restart Forwarder
sudo /opt/splunkforwarder/bin/splunk restart
________________________________________
Step 15: Verify Suricata Logs in Splunk
Open Splunk:
http://localhost:8000
Search:
source="/var/log/suricata/eve.json"
or
suricata
________________________________________
